column3: Built NEW.  Installed NEW Iridium SIM Card.
Successfully tested all MET sensor inputs, RF modem, IM data, and GPS.
Ran Bench current drain test for 4 days with version 2.01, 170530 firmware, RF modem turned off, 13.62mA Average.
Tested internal Iridium antenna by doing an XMIT outside, which successfully registered and sent dummy files.

Tried to use outside on test for IO1-18, but did multiple XMIT commands, and system registered, but everytime got an error message "no connect message received".  Not sure if this is a TFLEX0053 system problem, or an Iridium problem.
Back from IO2-18-RB, NOT USED, not deployed at 12S-67E due to bad weather on site.
Installed metal SS standoffs on bottom of circuit board stack.
Ran Bench current drain test for 4 days with version 2.01, 170530 firmware, RF modem turned off, 12.99mA Average.
Successfully tested GPS and XMIT commands outside on the internal antennas.
